  "text": "Interneurons of the DG degenerate in the hilus and the molecular layer but somatic inhibition of GCs is apparently spared [CITATION_1] . Here we refrain from reviewing TLE-related interneuron numbers, as respective cell counting studies mostly rely on Ca binding proteins which themselves change in TLE as shown by [CITATION_2] ; for review see [CITATION_3] . With respect to ion channels of interneurons in the hilus, a decrease of voltagegated Na type 1 (Na v 1) channels [CITATION_4] and an increase of Ca v 1 channels [CITATION_5] had been reported. Interestingly, in basket cell interneurons of the DG, tonic GABA A currents are homeostatically adjusted in sPilo rats .",
